        "stdout": "## Summary\n\nAddressed the **in-scope** review items (only `agent_fleet/`). Out-of-scope items (`tests/`, `docs/`) were left unchanged per the workstream constraint.\n\n### Changes\n\n**`agent_fleet/personas.py`**\n- Added `_resolve_persona_prompt_path()` \u2014 same resolution order as `YamlPersonaResolver.load()` (loadout \u2192 stub \u2192 skill \u2192 prompt).\n- Updated `persona_prompt_resolves()` to use it so prune does not drop loadout-backed personas (e.g. `coder` with a missing YAML prompt but a valid `coder.loadout.yaml` stub).\n- Refactored `load()` to call the shared helper (no behavior change intended).\n\n**`agent_fleet/cli.py`**\n- Wired `agent-fleet personas --prune` to `prune_fleet_yaml_personas()` (defaults to `default_fleet_config_path()`).\n- Updated `--config` help text for the preferred `~/.agent-fleet/fleet.yaml` path.\n\n**`agent_fleet/config.py`**\n- Added `default_fleet_config_path()` (prefer `~/.agent-fleet/fleet.yaml`, then legacy Hermes path).\n- `load_fleet_config()` uses it when no path is given.\n\n### Verification\n\n| Check | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| `pytest -q` | **272 passed**, 1 skipped |\n| `ruff check agent_fleet tests` | **All checks passed** |\n| Manual prune/loadout script | `coder` kept (loadout stub); `ghost` pruned; `YamlPersonaResolver.load(\"coder\")` OK |\n| `agent-fleet --help` | `personas` and `workstream` subcommands present |\n\n**Regression note:** No new pytest file (scope). Before the fix, `persona_prompt_resolves(\"coder\", PersonaSpec(prompt=\"definitely-missing.md\"), \u2026)` would be `False` and prune would remove `coder`; after the fix it stays and only `ghost` is pruned.\n\n### Still open (other workstreams)\n\n- `tests/test_persona_registry.py`, `docs/FLEET-CONFIG.md` duplicate section, `agents/personas` CI coverage \u2014 outside `agent_fleet/` scope for this run.",
